how can i help my pet boxer with psychological problems we rescued our dog from his previous owner who didn't treat him too well we have other dogs and he gets jealous of them he develops wounds as manifestation of his jealousy giving him dog treats aren't enough anymore what can i do to help our poor doggie this must be ask about the boxer day love to see that people love the breed as much as i do first off we need to take into consideration that he has been previously mistreated which will require extra patience and attention start from scratch as if he were still a baby with your obedience training use a leash and keep him under control take him away from the other dogs and do this so that he can focus as i said to another person here earlier dogs can and will hurt themselves if really stressed just like people how do the other dogs rest of the dogs that you have treat him they also might need to be put in check while your working with your boxer this breed is a very contact breed they like to feel closeness as much as possible most of them you will just have to show him and all your other dogs that you are the boss and will dictate to them what is allowed in the pack but unlike some of the other answers please be kind and attentive i have seen some of the most awful cases of abuse and neglect good for you for rescuing this dog it is people like you that make our pets lifes a better place take it slow and take it easy spend quality alone time give love and go overboard with praise when he displays the behavior you expect update us all on your progress good luck and take care Dog training German Shepherd Dog Housebreaking Dog Dog agility Domestic rabbit Obedience training Working dog Pet skunk Golden Retriever Havanese Shetland Sheepdog Keeshond Pit bull Fancy rat Zoophilia Social rule Nintendogs Infantilism Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers Maison Ikkoku The Critic Cat Iditarod Ron Weasley American Pit Bull Terrier Labrador Retriever Jealousy Rule of St Benedict Peking